In general, tigers are solitary and territorial animals,  
requiring a large home range of between 500 to 620  
square miles. In captivity, these animals need lots of  
space. Tigers only come together with other tigers  
during the spring mating season. Mother tigers will  
generally associate only with their young. Tigers  
reproduce well in captivity. 
 
